_VÃ¦r hilset!_

I'm **Emil Rivera-Thorsen**, astronomer and researcher at the [Oscar
Klein Center](http://okc.albanova.se) in Stockholm, Sweden. I research the nature and evolution of young,
vigorously star-forming "Starburst" galaxies in the distant Universe, using some
of the world's most advanced telescopes, including ESO's Very Large Telescope in
Paranal, Chile; the [Hubble Space Telescope](https://esahubble.org/), the [James Webb Space Telescope](https://www.jwst.nasa.gov/), and
the Indian UV-observatory [Astrosat](https://www.isro.gov.in/astrosat-0).
